title: New ‘Steve Jobs’ movie opening weekend a box-office ‘bloodbath’ - newsR
text: The new Steve Jobs movie, starring Michael Fassbender as Jobs, has been called a “box-office bloodbath” after it came in at a measly 8th place on the opening weekend — grossing just $7.3 million. That’s a surprise, because the movie was widely acclaimed by critics. The flop also comes as a surprise because it’s from the same […] »
